Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents a pipeline for learning motion control policies for a mobile robot. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a learning paradigm for policy transfer. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper involves learning a generative model to refine simulator outputs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with motion control policies for a mobile robot. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the multi-modal state estimation of the robot may involve visual perception.
